I am trying to get replay watch working with advantage scope. So far I am able to run the replay sim and get a new simulation log, I am also able to change some code in the src, then run the replay sim and the replay outputs change accordingly.

The issue comes when I try to run replayWatch. I open a log on advantage scope, and according to the docs it says to run “gradle.bat replayWatch” for a windows system, which I am on, the terminal reports that it could not find the command, so I run the command in the docs for macOS/Linux: “./gradlew replayWatch” here it appears to be working by presenting green loading bar like it appears when building your code. It runs through some commands but when it gets to 83% on executing it says replay active, and after a couple of seconds it goes to replay failed. It sits on replay failed for a bit then it keeps trying, then failing. This goes on apparantly forever until I am forced to ctrl + c on the terminal and terminate the process.

I have also copied the skeleton template. I added this line to the robot.java Logger.addDataReceiver(new WPILOGWriter()); then I ran the sim with the gui to create a log. I opened the log on advantage scope and ran ./gradlew replayWatch. this time the executing goes to 93% and it says replay active… and it just sits there never saying replay finished.

Any help is appreciated, thank you!

